column5: Lake Trout that is. It's what's for dinner. My BBQ specialty Dave's Fiery Texas Trout. Drizzled with liquid smoke and then spiced up with a variety of Tex Mex and South West spices.    Becomes    And finally
Finally.... someone posting a BBQ'ed Trout
Looks tasty now where is the pic of the fish with the skin on?
They sell that in Foodland up there Dave....
Must have been co-op or extra foods lol he did call me to go out even after the auger was fixed lol , it was minus 27 windchills last night
Sorry I meant he did not call me, I think he is focusing on getting his boat ready lol
Don't know if this is the one or not as he told me he got 6 or 8 lakers in the net on the weekend.

Yes. My buddy has a commercial license. I could get a personal use permit and net myself if I wanted to. Things are different up here.  FYI, there are only 16 commercial licensed fishermen operating on the lake. The lake is 27,200 sq kms and 480 kms long by 109 kms wide. It's also the deepest lake in North America @ 2,010 feet at it's deepest.
thats what i figured,  pretty cool.  that trout would be a fish of a lifetime for me.
I have heard of Tex-Mex but never Tex-Can. lol Looks a lot better than what I had for dinner. Enjoy.  Art
Low carb diet. Only 6gr of carbs in this meal.
